(21779,'cars','reference','detonation-frequency','en','Detonation Frequency','Detonation Frequency The reverberation resonance generated by detonation generally lies in the range between 2 and 12KHz.','beginner','Detonation Frequency The reverberation resonance generated by detonation generally lies in the range between 2 and 12KHz. The following equation can be used to estimate the detonation resonant frequency for a specific engine. 900 / (3.14 x cylinder radius) Where the resonant frequency is measured in Hertz and the cylinder radius in metres.','cars/reference/detonation-frequency/detonation-frequency.md','2026-06-15 22:15:12',0),
