(21781,'cars','reference','little-endian','en','Little Endian','Little Endian is the layout of multibyte values in memory used by many processors, including Intel x86\'s and OKI 66k\'s.','beginner','Little Endian is the layout of multi-byte values in memory used by many processors, including Intel x86\'s and OKI 66k\'s. Little Endian layout stores the ***least significant byte first***. For 16-bit values, the actual value is Second Byte*256 + First Byte','cars/reference/little-endian/little-endian.md','2026-06-15 22:15:12',0),
