(21870,'cars','rom','p13jdm','en','P13JDM','RAM Location Bytes Description Notes : : : : ROM Location Bytes Description Notes : : : : 2EC1 1 Rev Limit Desired RPM/45.','beginner','###  [RAM](/cars/reference/ram) \n\n| **Location** | **Bytes** | **Description** | **Notes** |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n|  |  |  |  |\n\n###  [ROM](/cars/rom/rom) \n\n| **Location** | **Bytes** | **Description** | **Notes** |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| 2EC1 | 1 | Rev Limit | Desired [RPM](/cars/sensors/rpm)/45.18 = some 8-bit decimal value. change to Hex and put in 2EC1 |','cars/rom/p13jdm/p13jdm.md','2026-06-15 22:15:12',0),
(21871,'cars','rom','p1j','en','P1J','P1J and P1K come from 9600 UK civics with D14 engines. Despite the years, those are OBDI ECUs and seem to be easyly convertable for VTEC Sorry for the...','intermediate','P1J and P1K come from 96-00 UK civics with D14 engines. Despite the years, those are OBDI [ECU](/cars/ecu/ecu)s and seem to be easyly convertable for VTEC Sorry for the bad images, please consult the page on [P1 K](/cars/rom/p1k) for better views of the [PCB](/cars/wiring/pcb). Those OBDI P1J or P1K [ECU](/cars/ecu/ecu)s share a strange board layout labeled as: \"2PU6098-4460P1 5 A8E-A3\", but get easyly chipped. VTEC converion seems easy, but is not yet tested.\n\n| **Attachment:** | **Modify:** | **Size:** | **Date:** | **Who:** | **Comment:** |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| ![](/pgmfi/wiki/assets/icn/bmp.gif) [DSC00055\\\\_small.jpg](DSC00055_small.jpg) | mod | 168080 | 29 Jan 2007 - 15:58 | 1net |  |\n| ![](/pgmfi/wiki/assets/icn/bmp.gif) [DSC00056\\\\_small.jpg](DSC00056_small.jpg) | mod | 176792 | 29 Jan 2007 - 16:00 | 1net |  |\n| ![](/pgmfi/wiki/assets/icn/bmp.gif) [DSC00057\\\\_small.jpg](DSC00057_small.jpg) | mod | 179335 | 29 Jan 2007 - 16:00 | 1net |  |\n| ![](/pgmfi/wiki/assets/icn/bmp.gif) [DSC00058\\\\_small.jpg](DSC00058_small.jpg) | mod | 158777 | 29 Jan 2007 - 16:01 | 1net |  |\n| ![](/pgmfi/wiki/assets/icn/bmp.gif) [DSC00054\\\\_small.jpg](DSC00054_small.jpg) | mod | 71125 | 29 Jan 2007 - 16:01 | 1net |  |','cars/rom/p1j/p1j.md','2026-06-15 22:15:12',0),
(21872,'cars','rom','p1k','en','P1K','P1J and P1K come from 9600 UK civics with D14 engines. Despite the years, those are OBDI ECUs and seem to be easyly convertable for VTEC Those OBDI P1J...','intermediate','P1J and P1K come from 96-00 UK civics with D14 engines. Despite the years, those are OBDI [ECU](/cars/ecu/ecu)s and seem to be easyly convertable for VTEC Those OBDI P1J or P1K [ECU](/cars/ecu/ecu)s share a strange board layout labeled as: \"2PU6098-4460P1 5 A8E-A3\", but get easyly chipped. VTEC converion seems easy, but is not yet tested.\n\n| **Attachment:** | **Modify:** | **Size:** | **Date:** | **Who:** | **Comment:** |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| ![](/pgmfi/wiki/assets/icn/bmp.gif) [DSC00132.JPG](DSC00132.JPG) | mod | 1229745 | 29 Jan 2007 - 16:21 | 1net |  |\n| ![](/pgmfi/wiki/assets/icn/bmp.gif) [DSC00134.JPG](DSC00134.JPG) | mod | 1239808 | 29 Jan 2007 - 16:22 | 1net |  |\n| ![](/pgmfi/wiki/assets/icn/bmp.gif) [DSC00135.JPG](DSC00135.JPG) | mod | 1242333 | 29 Jan 2007 - 16:24 | 1net |  |\n| ![](/pgmfi/wiki/assets/icn/bmp.gif) [DSC00141.JPG](DSC00141.JPG) | mod | 1264962 | 29 Jan 2007 - 16:25 | 1net | some hardly visible components |\n| ![](/pgmfi/wiki/assets/icn/bmp.gif) [DSC00150\\\\_small.jpg](DSC00150_small.jpg) | mod | 151431 | 29 Jan 2007 - 16:26 | 1net | how they\'re chipped |','cars/rom/p1k/p1k.md','2026-06-15 22:15:12',0),
(21873,'cars','rom','p61','en','P61','P61 9293 OBD1 USDM GSR B17A DOHC VTEC m66207215 Attachment: Modify: Size: Date: Who: Comment: : : : : : :','advanced','P61 92-93 [OBD1](/cars/wiring/obd1) [USDM](/cars/sensors/usdm) GSR B17A [DOHC](/cars/sensors/dohc) VTEC m66207-215\n\n| **Attachment:** | **Modify:** | **Size:** | **Date:** | **Who:** | **Comment:** |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| ![](/pgmfi/wiki/assets/icn/bmp.gif) [p61\\\\_knock\\\\_board\\\\_174.jpg](p61_knock_board_174.jpg) | mod | 820675 | 19 Sep 2006 - 18:10 | carotman | P61 External [ROM](/cars/rom/rom) Board |\n| ![](/pgmfi/wiki/assets/icn/else.gif) [p61\\\\_knock.BIN](p61_knock.BIN) | mod | 32768 | 19 Sep 2006 - 18:12 | carotman | BIN Extracted from the Extermal Knock Board |','cars/rom/p61/p61.md','2026-06-15 22:15:12',0),
(21874,'cars','rom','pe7','en','PE7','the PE7 came on 8587 EDM/USDM Civic/CRX Si (EW3/EW4 Vacuum advance) cars. Thanks to Mark Lamond for the scans.','beginner','the PE7 came on 85-87 [EDM](/cars/wiring/edm)/USDM Civic/CRX Si (EW3/EW4 Vacuum advance) cars. Thanks to Mark Lamond for the scans.\n\n- [PE7-682-87_Civic_Si.bin](PE7-682-87_Civic_Si.bin): [ROM](/cars/rom/rom) from a stock PE7-682 (European 87 Civic Si)\n\n| **Attachment:** | **Modify:** | **Size:** | **Date:** | **Who:** | **Comment:** |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| ![](/pgmfi/wiki/assets/icn/bmp.gif) [PE7-741\\\\_solder.jpg](PE7-741_solder.jpg) | mod | 3127695 | 17 Dec 2003 - 22:32 | The Admin | Scan of bottom (solder) side |\n| ![](/pgmfi/wiki/assets/icn/bmp.gif) [PE7-741\\\\_component.jpg](PE7-741_component.jpg) | mod | 2413694 | 17 Dec 2003 - 22:34 | The Admin | Scan of top (component) side |','cars/rom/pe7/pe7.md','2026-06-15 22:15:12',0),
