(21921,'cars','sensors','c-carry-bit','en','C Carry Bit','In the 8051 architecture, \"C\" is the name of the carry bit. When an arithmetic operation overflows, the carry bit is set to keep track of this change.','advanced','In the 8051 architecture, \"C\" is the name of the carry bit. When an arithmetic operation overflows, the carry bit is set to keep track of this change. This bit is also frequently used as a storage space for transferring bits. This goes for the Oki 66k architecture as well; the MB C, x and MB x, C instructions allow easy access to the carry flag.','cars/sensors/c-carry-bit/c-carry-bit.md','2026-06-15 22:15:12',0),
(21922,'cars','sensors','c144','en','`C144`','C144 is a NPN switching transistor. It has been successfully replaced with C2785 (and its replacements).','beginner','`C144` is a NPN switching transistor. It has been successfully replaced with [C2785](/cars/sensors/c2785) (and its replacements).','cars/sensors/c144/c144.md','2026-06-15 22:15:12',0),
(21923,'cars','sensors','c2785','en','C2785','C2785 is a high speed NPN switching transistor Thanks to Javier (dohcvtec) for a handy C2785 replacement.','beginner','C2785 is a high speed NPN switching transistor Thanks to Javier (dohcvtec) for a handy C2785 replacement. This also works for `C144`. C2785===> NTE2361 ===> 2SD1423ARACT-ND (Digikey Panasonic)====>C2458Y [Datasheet here.](http://www.nteinc.com/specs/2300to2399/pdf/nte2361.pdf)','cars/sensors/c2785/c2785.md','2026-06-15 22:15:12',0),
