(21932,'cars','sensors','dohc','en','DOHC','Dual ~OverHead Cam motors have a seperate Cam Shaft for both Intake Valves and Exhaust Valves. See also SOHC.','beginner','Dual ~OverHead Cam motors have a seperate Cam Shaft for both Intake Valves and Exhaust Valves. See also [SOHC](/cars/sensors/sohc).','cars/sensors/dohc/dohc.md','2026-06-15 22:15:12',0),
(21933,'cars','sensors','dpfi','en','DPFI','(Dual Point Fuel Injection) Please refer to the explanation of Dual Point.','beginner','([Dual Point](/cars/sensors/dual-point) Fuel Injection) Please refer to the explanation of [Dual Point](/cars/sensors/dual-point).','cars/sensors/dpfi/dpfi.md','2026-06-15 22:15:12',0),
(21934,'cars','sensors','dual-point','en','Dual Point','Dual Point is used for refering to the DPFI ( DualPoint Fuel Injection) motors and ECUs. It is essencialy the next generation of carbs.','intermediate','[Dual Point](/cars/sensors/dual-point) is used for refering to the [DPFI](/cars/sensors/dpfi) ( Dual-Point Fuel Injection) motors and [ECU](/cars/ecu/ecu)s. It is essencialy the next generation of carbs. The fuel is injected with 2 injectors in the common manifold. Which ever cylinder is on the intake stroke sucks the fuel. Fuel separation, bad fuel atomization and delivery are only some of the problems [DPFI](/cars/sensors/dpfi) systems have and those are the primary reasons they deliver less power then their [MPFI](/cars/sensors/mpfi) brothers. Software for the [DPFI](/cars/sensors/dpfi) [ECU](/cars/ecu/ecu)s like the PM5/PM9 and P04 is not developed as they are considered useless for power and tuning mods. Consider doing an [MPFI](/cars/sensors/mpfi) swap if you\'re on the quest for power.','cars/sensors/dual-point/dual-point.md','2026-06-15 22:15:12',0),
(21935,'cars','sensors','ect','en','ECT','Engine Coolant Temperature','beginner','[Engine Coolant Temperature](/cars/diagnostics/engine-coolant-temperature)','cars/sensors/ect/ect.md','2026-06-15 22:15:12',0),
(21936,'cars','sensors','ecu-sensors','en','ECU Sensors','The input sensors a Honda ECU reads to run fuel and ignition.','beginner','Sensors present on almost all honda motors:\n\n- [Crankshaft Position Sensor](/cars/ignition/crankshaft-position-sensor) - Determines timing for fuel injection and ignition of `each` cylinder and also detects engine speed.\n- Top Dead Center Sensor - Determines ignition timing at start-up (cranking) and when crank angle is abnormal.\n- [Cylinder Position Sensor](/cars/sensors/cylinder-position-sensor) - Detects position of #1 cylinder for sequential spark ignition to `each` cylinder.\n- Engine Coolant Temperature - or \'\'ECT\'\' thermocouple input for engine coolant temperature\n- [Intake Air Temperature Sensor](/cars/sensors/intake-air-temperature-sensor) - or \'\'IAT\'\' thermocouple input for intake air temperature\n- Map Sensor - Manifold Absolute Pressure Sensor, allows [ECU](/cars/ecu/ecu) to adjust Air Fuel Ratio based on density of intake air\n- Oxygen Sensor - Measures oxygen content of exhaust gas\n- Pressure Atmosphere - or \'\'PA\'\' or \'\'Barometric Pressure Sensor\'\' measures atmospheric pressure.\n- TPS Sensor - Throttle Position Sensor\n- Vehicle Speed Sensor - or \'\'VSS\'\' measures how fast ***axles*** are turning\n- Idle Air Control Valve / Electronic Air Control Vale - Or \'\'IAC/EACV\'\' Helps control idle\n\nOptional sensors: - Electrical Load Detector - or \'\'ELD\'\' present in most US cars to measure how much electrical load there is\n- [Knock Sensor](/cars/ignition/knock-sensor) - A microphone-like device to listen for Pre Ignition, or knocking in DOHC VTEC motors.\n- Pa Sensor - Atmospheric Pressure sensor\n- VTEC Solenoid = solenoid to route oil flow to activate VTEC (on VTEC motors only :) )\n\n---\n\nOther [ECU](/cars/ecu/ecu) Sensors not usually present on honda motors: - Maf Sensor','cars/sensors/ecu-sensors/ecu-sensors.md','2026-06-15 22:15:12',0),
(21937,'cars','sensors','electrical-load-detector','en','Electrical Load Detector','Electronic Load Detector measures electrical load used to determine if the alternator should be in low or high output mode.','beginner','Electronic Load Detector measures electrical load - used to determine if the alternator should be in low or high output mode. Since Hondas are running so lean at idle, virtually any load will cause the idle to drop. Even small electrical loads, such as the turn signals, will cause the idle to fluctuate. The electrical load detector (ELD) was added to later model Hondas to monitor for any significant electrical loads. It sends a warning signal to the ECM before the load has a chance to effect the idle. The ECM makes slight adjustments to the idle air control (IAC) valve, injector PW, and ignition timing to compensate for the electrical load.','cars/sensors/electrical-load-detector/electrical-load-detector.md','2026-06-15 22:15:12',0),
(21938,'cars','sensors','electronic-advance','en','Electronic Advance','Electronic Advance refers to a motor setup where Spark Advance can be controlled electronically by the ECU.','beginner','[Electronic Advance](/cars/sensors/electronic-advance) refers to a motor setup where [Spark Advance](/cars/sensors/spark-advance) can be controlled electronically by the [ECU](/cars/ecu/ecu). Electronic Advance replaced [Vacuum Advance](/cars/sensors/vacuum-advance) because it is much more flexible for tuning, and allows much better control of the motor. Distributorless direct-fire distributorless ignitions are largely replacing electronic advance now (early 2004).','cars/sensors/electronic-advance/electronic-advance.md','2026-06-15 22:15:12',0),
(21939,'cars','sensors','electronic-advance-distributors','en','Electronic Advance Distributors','Electronic Advance Distributors are distributors where the amount of Spark Advance can be controlled electronically by the ECU.','beginner','Electronic Advance [Distributors](/cars/sensors/distributors) are distributors where the amount of [Spark Advance](/cars/sensors/spark-advance) can be controlled electronically by the [ECU](/cars/ecu/ecu).','cars/sensors/electronic-advance-distributors/electronic-advance-distributors.md','2026-06-15 22:15:12',0),
(21940,'cars','sensors','electronic-air-control-vale','en','Electronic Air Control Vale','See : Idle Air Control Valve','beginner','See : [Idle Air Control Valve](/cars/sensors/idle-air-control-valve)','cars/sensors/electronic-air-control-vale/electronic-air-control-vale.md','2026-06-15 22:15:12',0),
