(21942,'cars','sensors','erm','en','ERM','see Uber Data ERM','beginner','see [Uber Data ERM](/cars/rom/uber-data-erm)','cars/sensors/erm/erm.md','2026-06-15 22:15:12',0),
(21943,'cars','sensors','fuel-octane','en','Fuel Octane','Fuel \"Octane\" is a measure of gasoline\'s resistance to Pre Ignition. the Gasoline FAQ explains all you ever wanted to know about gasoline, including a...','beginner','Fuel \"Octane\" is a measure of gasoline\'s resistance to [Pre Ignition](/cars/diagnostics/pre-ignition). the [Gasoline FAQ ](http://web.archive.org/web/20260327020540/http://www.faqs.org/faqs/autos/gasoline-faq/) explains all you ever wanted to know about gasoline, including a very good section on how octane is measured, what octane numbers mean and what you can do to increase the octane rating of gasoline.','cars/sensors/fuel-octane/fuel-octane.md','2026-06-15 22:15:12',0),
(21944,'cars','sensors','future-active','en','Future Active','Future Active is a major electronic parts distributor. They sell both the 27SF256 and Aries lowprofile ZIF cheap.','beginner','[Future Active](http://www.future-active.com) is a major electronic parts distributor. They sell both the `27SF256` and Aries low-profile [ZIF](/cars/rom/zif) cheap.','cars/sensors/future-active/future-active.md','2026-06-15 22:15:12',0),
(21945,'cars','sensors','helms-manual','en','Helms Manual','Helm Inc. http://web.archive.org/web/20260613155229/https://www/.helminc.com The distributor of the Honda Service Manual. EF (8891 Civic/CRX), EG (9295 Civic), DA (9093 Integra), DC (9401 Integra) http://web.archive.org/web/20260613155229/https://www/.','beginner','Helm Inc. [http://web.archive.org/web/20260613155229/https://www/.helminc.com](http://web.archive.org/web/20260613155229/https://www/.helminc.com) The distributor of the Honda [Service Manual](/cars/sensors/service-manual). EF (88-91 Civic/CRX), EG (92-95 Civic), DA (90-93 Integra), DC (94-01 Integra) [http://web.archive.org/web/20260613155229/https://www/.hybridgarage.com/tech/manuals](http://web.archive.org/web/20260613155229/https://www/.hybridgarage.com/tech/manuals)','cars/sensors/helms-manual/helms-manual.md','2026-06-15 22:15:12',0),
(21946,'cars','sensors','high-cam','en','High Cam','in a VTEC motor, the High Cam is used at higher RPMs. This Cam Shaft is generally optimized for power and higherRPMs.','beginner','in a [VTEC](/cars/sensors/vtec) motor, the [High Cam](/cars/sensors/high-cam) is used at higher [RPM](/cars/sensors/rpm)s. This Cam Shaft is generally optimized for power and higher-RPMs. See also: [Low Cam](/cars/sensors/low-cam)\n\n- [High Cam](/cars/sensors/high-cam) of VTEC camshaft: \n     ![vtechigh.gif](vtechigh.gif)\n\n| **Attachment:** | **Modify:** | **Size:** | **Date:** | **Who:** | **Comment:** |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| ![](/pgmfi/wiki/assets/icn/bmp.gif) [vtechigh.gif](vtechigh.gif) | mod | 8630 | 30 Mar 2004 - 08:08 | tekphobia | [High Cam](/cars/sensors/high-cam) of VTEC camshaft |','cars/sensors/high-cam/high-cam.md','2026-06-15 22:15:12',0),
(21947,'cars','sensors','iab','en','IAB','Intake Air Butterflies a valve that opens and closes to switch between two available passages in the intake manifold.','beginner','Intake Air Butterflies - a valve that opens and closes to switch between two available passages in the intake manifold. This is done to allow the use of a longer runner at low [RPM](/cars/sensors/rpm)s for increased torque and a short runner at high [RPM](/cars/sensors/rpm)s for more power. Found on GSR and H22A intake manifolds.','cars/sensors/iab/iab.md','2026-06-15 22:15:12',0),
(21948,'cars','sensors','iat','en','IAT','See Intake Air Temperature Sensor','beginner','See [Intake Air Temperature Sensor](/cars/sensors/intake-air-temperature-sensor)','cars/sensors/iat/iat.md','2026-06-15 22:15:12',0),
(21949,'cars','sensors','idle-air-control-valve','en','Idle Air Control Valve','The Idle air control valve, or IACV regulates the car\'s idle based on the coolant temperature. Target idle settings vs.','beginner','The Idle air control valve, or IACV regulates the car\'s idle based on the coolant temperature.\n\n- Target idle settings vs. [ECT](/cars/sensors/ect): \n     ![honda_EACV_target_idle.jpg](honda_EACV_target_idle.jpg)\n\nNote: this is [ECU](/cars/ecu/ecu) controlled and can be altered.\n\n## Troubleshooting & Repair\n\nIf you are experiencing a persistent Check Engine Light Code 14 or a very low/erratic idle, your ECU\'s internal driver circuit may be blown. See the [IACV Circuit Fix - R58 & R59](/cars/diagnostics/iacv-circuit-fix-r58-r59) guide for diagnostic steps and component repair details.','cars/sensors/idle-air-control-valve/idle-air-control-valve.md','2026-06-15 22:15:12',0),
(21950,'cars','sensors','intake-air-temperature-sensor','en','Intake Air Temperature Sensor','The intake air temperature (IAT) sensor and its effect on fueling.',NULL,'[Intake Air Temperature Sensor](/cars/sensors/intake-air-temperature-sensor) The intake air temperature sensor reads the temperature of air flowing into the motor. - graph of resistance / temperature for stock IAT: \n     ![honda_stock_IAT.jpg](honda_stock_IAT.jpg)\n\nListed below is honda\'s table for Intake air temps and voltage output   **TEMP in °C**  **IAT voltage (volts)**  100  0  95  0.156  89  0.312  83  0.468  77  0.624  72  0.780  66  0.936  61  1.090  56  1.248  51  1.404  46  1.560  42  1.716  38  1.872  34  2.028  31  2.184  27  2.340  24  2.496  21  2.652  18  2.808  15  2.964  12  3.120  9  3.276  7  3.432  5  3.588  3  3.744  1  3.900  -1  4.056  -3  4.212  -5  4.368  -6  4.524  -7  4.680  -9  4.836  -10  4.992 - All table values were establisted and tested by AEM corp','cars/sensors/intake-air-temperature-sensor/intake-air-temperature-sensor.md','2026-06-15 22:15:12',0),
