(22018,'cars','sensors','rev-limiter','en','Rev Limiter','A rev limiter limits how fast a motor can spin. Most honda ECUs implement a Fuel Cut Rev Limiter.','beginner','A rev limiter limits how fast a motor can spin. Most honda [ECU](/cars/ecu/ecu)s implement a [Fuel Cut](/cars/rom/fuel-cut) [Rev Limiter](/cars/sensors/rev-limiter).','cars/sensors/rev-limiter/rev-limiter.md','2026-06-15 22:15:12',0),
(22019,'cars','sensors','revolutions-per-minute','en','Revolutions Per Minute','Revolutions Per Minute means how many times the engine spins in a minute.','beginner','[Revolutions Per Minute](/cars/sensors/revolutions-per-minute) means how many times the engine spins in a minute.','cars/sensors/revolutions-per-minute/revolutions-per-minute.md','2026-06-15 22:15:12',0),
(22020,'cars','sensors','rpm','en','RPM','Revolutions Per Minute means how many times the engine spins in a minute. Taken off the CKP (Crank Shaft Position Sensor) 2 pulses per 1 revolution.','beginner','[Revolutions Per Minute](/cars/sensors/revolutions-per-minute) means how many times the engine spins in a minute. Taken off the CKP (Crank Shaft Position Sensor) 2 pulses per 1 revolution. https://web.archive.org/web/http://www.pgmfi.org/phorum/download.php/13,398/pulses%20-%20rpm.gif','cars/sensors/rpm/rpm.md','2026-06-15 22:15:12',0),
(22021,'cars','sensors','rs232','en','RS232','RS232 signalling is a serial communication protocol that uses +12/12v signalling. It is commonly found on PC serial ports.','beginner','RS232 signalling is a [serial communication](/cars/tuning/serial-communication) protocol that uses +12/-12v signalling. It is commonly found on PC serial ports.','cars/sensors/rs232/rs232.md','2026-06-15 22:15:12',0),
(22022,'cars','sensors','rtfm','en','RTFM','RTFM is a acronym for \"Read The Fucking Manual\". If you are told this... you should probbabally do some searching around WIKI and the forums , because...','beginner','[RTFM](/cars/sensors/rtfm) is a acronym for \"Read The Fucking Manual\". If you are told this... you should probbabally do some searching around [WIKI ](https://web.archive.org/web/http://wiki.pgmfi.org) and the [forums ](), because your answer has most likely already been covered, and in one of these places.','cars/sensors/rtfm/rtfm.md','2026-06-15 22:15:12',0),
(22023,'cars','sensors','rtp','en','RTP','Real Time Programmability The ability to change the program/tuning of an ECU while the ECU is running the motor.','beginner','Real Time Programmability The ability to change the program/tuning of an [ECU](/cars/ecu/ecu) while the [ECU](/cars/ecu/ecu) is running the motor. Currently, only the [Zdyne](http://web.archive.org/web/20180503200132/http://zdyne.com:80/) SECU Gold and the [AEM](http://web.archive.org/web/20230925104126/https://www.aempower.com/) [EMS Standalone](http://web.archive.org/web/20060825170912/http://web.archive.org/web/20230925104126/https://www.aempower.com/:80/product_ems.asp) support this. Achieving real time programmability with a stock [ECU](/cars/ecu/ecu) is a significant goal for the PGMFI project.','cars/sensors/rtp/rtp.md','2026-06-15 22:15:12',0),
(22024,'cars','sensors','saturated-injectors','en','Saturated Injectors','Saturated Injectors aka High Impedance InjectorsImpedance typically 1216ohms. At 12volts, this is a draw of ~1.','beginner','[Saturated Injectors](/cars/sensors/saturated-injectors) aka [High Impedance Injectors](/cars/fueling/high-impedance-injectors)Impedance typically 12-16ohms. At 12volts, this is a draw of ~1-.75 amps. The low current helps keep the injectors cool. The saturated injectors see a steady 12volts, and ground is modulated to produce pulsing. These are the stock style of injector for [OBD1](/cars/wiring/obd1) and up hondas, so no resistor box is needed.','cars/sensors/saturated-injectors/saturated-injectors.md','2026-06-15 22:15:12',0),
(22025,'cars','sensors','sectors','en','sectors','A sector is a block of data. It can vary in size.','beginner','A sector is a block of data. It can vary in size.','cars/sensors/sectors/sectors.md','2026-06-15 22:15:12',0),
