(22027,'cars','sensors','sohc','en','SOHC','Single ~OverHead Cam motors have a single Cam Shaft that opens both Intake Valves and Exhaust Valves. Most \"D\" series motors are SOHC. See also: DOHC','beginner','Single ~OverHead Cam motors have a single Cam Shaft that opens both Intake Valves and Exhaust Valves. Most \"D\" series motors are [SOHC](/cars/sensors/sohc). See also: [DOHC](/cars/sensors/dohc)','cars/sensors/sohc/sohc.md','2026-06-15 22:15:12',0),
(22028,'cars','sensors','spark-advance','en','Spark Advance','Spark Advance refers to how many degrees of angular rotation happen between when the spark is set off and the motor reaches TDC','beginner','Spark Advance refers to how many degrees of angular rotation happen between when the spark is set off and the motor reaches [TDC](/cars/sensors/tdc)','cars/sensors/spark-advance/spark-advance.md','2026-06-15 22:15:12',0),
(22029,'cars','sensors','spark-cut','en','Spark Cut','A spark cut is when fuel continues to be supplied to the motor but no sparks are triggered to ignite the fuel.','beginner','A spark cut is when fuel continues to be supplied to the motor but no sparks are triggered to ignite the fuel. This is a good way to shoot flames out of the back of a hot exhaust. [Spark Cut](/cars/sensors/spark-cut)s are generally implemented by aftermarket ignition systems. The stock [ECU](/cars/ecu/ecu) uses a [Fuel Cut](/cars/rom/fuel-cut) for [Rev Limiter](/cars/sensors/rev-limiter)s and [Speed Limiter](/cars/diagnostics/speed-limiter)s.','cars/sensors/spark-cut/spark-cut.md','2026-06-15 22:15:12',0),
(22030,'cars','sensors','sram','en','SRAM','Understand how static RAM retains data without a refresh cycle while power remains connected.','beginner','Static [RAM](/cars/reference/ram), or SRAM, is fast, does not require a refresh cycle, and retains information as long as it has power.','cars/sensors/sram/sram.md','2026-06-15 22:15:12',0),
